<tr><td class=3D"center">
  <div class=3D"full_width shadow justify table">
  <p><strong>The equation solver finds solutions to mathematical equations =
using symbolic computation and algebraic manipulation techniques.</strong> =
Equations can range from simple linear equations to complex polynomial, exp=
onential, trigonometric, and logarithmic equations.</p>
  <p>The solving process applies algebraic principles including isolation o=
f variables, factoring, substitution, and inverse operations to find exact =
solutions where possible. For example, solving x=C2=B2 - 5x + 6 =3D 0 invol=
ves factoring to (x-2)(x-3) =3D 0, yielding solutions x =3D 2 and x =3D 3. =
The solver can handle systems of equations using elimination, substitution,=
 and matrix methods.</p>
  <p>Applications include engineering problem-solving, physics calculations=
, optimization problems, and mathematical modeling. The solver provides ste=
p-by-step solutions when possible, helping users understand the mathematica=
l reasoning behind each solution method.</p>
